   <S PAR='246' RSNT='1' SNO='246'>He has said it Himself, and everything is settled.</S>
   <S PAR='247' RSNT='1' SNO='247'>What more is there to worry about?</S>
   <S PAR='248' RSNT='1' SNO='248'>What are our feelings worth?</S>
   <S PAR='249' RSNT='1' SNO='249'>What are man s ideas worth?</S>
   <S PAR='250' RSNT='1' SNO='250'>If God says that we are saved, it is enough.</S>
   <S PAR='251' RSNT='1' SNO='251'>His Word is the final verdict.</S>
   <S PAR='252' RSNT='1' SNO='252'>Since God has graciously declared His faithfulness, we should accept His Word without doubt.</S>
   <S PAR='253' RSNT='1' SNO='253'>Some may say, What was said may be true.</S>
   <S PAR='254' RSNT='1' SNO='254'>But I am afraid that my faith is not perfect, and therefore, I cannot be saved.</S>
   <S PAR='255' RSNT='1' SNO='255'>The Bible only makes a distinction between believing and not believing.</S>
